{"author":{"id":"ca1d6d5abb83fed484d327d8971a2c702c9f45815e3e29215cd302d6076cba2c"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1747369422,"nonce":"k2sBQud3MmRKPgxAzSp8sOoDndM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s623GJA","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6986","origin":"github"},"title":"samtools_depth should map over datasets","message":"The `samtools_depth` treats a dataset collection as many bams. I think this not really standard usage of `samtools depth` which is (I think) performed on individual bams separately. This wouldnt be a big problem if the item names in the collection are transferred over into the output depth file. However this is not possible as samtools depth does not output header information. The end result is a not useful output.\n\nThe solution is allow the user to select single or multiple bams, similar to how [samtools_coverage](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/main/tool_collections/samtools/samtools_coverage/samtools_coverage.xml) handles this situation.","files":null}]}